<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4159 The Law Of God Is Good And Wise (G major, ends on Em)
Key: G (1 sharp F#). Hymn has strong modal/minor character: opens and closes on vi=Em.

This creates an Aeolian feel within G major — the arrangement treats Em as
the tonal center of phrases 1 and 3, with I=G appearing only at m.8 (center).

Non-diatonic subs:
  Eb in m.2 → Em (vi) same root area
  D# in m.10 → Em sustained (same chord, passing tone in melody only)

VOICING PATTERNS:
vi "334" opens (E2-B2-E3-G3) — modal dark color
iii "333" Bm in m.2 with F#3 for richer sound
Sequential ii→V→I in mm.4-5 (Am→D→G) — classic resolution
iii→IV in m.6 (Bm→C) for momentary brightness
Final vi: E5 in RH top voice for high resolution on Em

VOICE LEADING:
Inner B descends: B4(m1)→D4(m2)→B3(m3)→C4(m3)→A3(m4)→F#4(m5)→D4(m6)→D5(m7)→B4(m8)→B4(m10)
Consistent contrary motion between hands throughout.

TEXTURE ARC:
mm.1-3: Quiet, modal entry on Em, 2-note RH
mm.4-5: ii→V→I brightening in middle section
mm.6-7: iii→IV→V buildup to I (m.8) central cadence
mm.8: Full I sustained — only moment of pure major brightness
mm.9-10: Return to minor via C→D→Em. E5 in RH final note.
-->
